I3C - Improved Inter-Integrated Circuit
mcu » apollo330P

Detailed Description

Purpose: This module provides a high-level interface for the I3C (Improved Inter-Integrated Circuit) peripheral in Apollo5 devices. It supports advanced communication features beyond traditional I2C while maintaining backward compatibility.

Key Features

  1. High Speed: Support for higher data rates than I2C.
  2. Hot-Join: Dynamic attachment of new devices.
  3. In-Band Interrupts: Device-initiated communication.
  4. Multi-Protocol: I3C and legacy I2C support.
  5. Advanced Control: Enhanced command and data handling.

Functionality

  • Initialize and configure I3C interface
  • Support multiple transfer modes
  • Handle dynamic addressing
  • Process in-band interrupts
  • Manage device discovery

Usage

  1. Configure I3C controller parameters
  2. Set up device addressing and discovery
  3. Perform data transfers
  4. Handle device events and interrupts

Configuration

  • Speed Modes: Configure communication speeds
  • Address Settings: Set up device addressing
  • Transfer Options: Configure data transfer modes
  • Interrupt Handling: Set up event processing
